description:
Next, we travel to Paris Hill, Maine. In this quiet and rural location, teenagers from three families followed the Protestant principle of being true to their conscience and scripture. Marion Stowell, J N Andrews and Cyprian Stevens decided to keep the Sabbath, a decision that their parents would follow them in and one that would take them all over the US and the world in missionary work for God.

To find out more about the youth of Paris Hill Maine please read our extended article on our website.
https://lineagejourney.com/read/the-sabbath-and-the-youth-of-paris-hill-maine
